sudo apt-get install ibus-pinyin

screen capture
sudo apt-get install scrot

pdf and ebook reader
sudo apt-get install okular

remove and clean
sudo apt-get remove [package name]
sudo apt-get purge [package name]
sudo apt-get clean

purge orphaned files
sudo apt-get autoremove
sudo apt-get --purge -y autoremove

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get dist-upgrade
sudo apt-get install -y rpi-chromium-mods
sudo apt-get install -y python-sense-emu python3-sense-emu
sudo apt-get install -y python-sense-emu-doc realvnc-vnc-viewer

for those upgrading your current Raspbian system, who don't use xrdp for remote access, but want to enable RealVNC, enter the following command:
sudo apt-get install -y realvnc-vnc-server
If you do use xrdp, you can either keep using it or disable it and before enabling RealVNC.

sudo apt install cups cups-ipp-utils system-config-printer printer-driver-cups-pdf

sudo apt-get update
Once apt is updated, you can upgrade your Raspbian distribution.
$ sudo apt-get dist-upgrade

